Former Western Cape top cop, Jeremy Vearey, is slamming the SAPS for firing him. He was fired after a disciplinary hearing for allegedly criticising National Police Commissioner, Khehla Sitole, on Facebook. Courtesy #DStv403 CAPE TOWN - Former Western Cape top cop Jeremy Vearey says his disciplinary hearing was nothing but a witch hunt. Vearey was axed after a disciplinary hearing, for allegedly criticising National Police Commissioner Khehla Sitole on Facebook. Watch the video above for more on this story.